"title": "8611: prayer, for others",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8611",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Believers should pray, not only for their own needs, but for those of others. Scripture provides many examples of intercession, and commends it as pleasing to God.</p>\n<h2>Believers must value others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:3-Phil2:4\">PHP 2:3–2:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of praying for others</h2>\n<h3>Moses prays for the Israelites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:18-Deut9:19\">DEU 9:18–9:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:9-Exod32:14\">EXO 32:9–32:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:9\">EXO 34:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:11-Num14:19\">NUM 14:11–14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:25-Deut9:29\">DEU 9:25–9:29</a></p>\n<h3>Samuel prays for Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:5-1Sam7:9\">1SA 7:5–7:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:19-1Sam12:23\">1SA 12:19–12:23</a></p>\n<h3>Job prays for his friends</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:10\">JOB 42:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jeremiah prays for Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:16\">JER 7:16</a></strong> <em>God forbade the prophet Jeremiah to pray for his people because they were unrepentant sinners.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:14\">JER 11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:11\">JER 14:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ intercedes for believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:12\">ISA 53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1\">1JN 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit intercedes for believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:27\">ROM 8:26–8:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Christians are to intercede for others</h2>\n<h3>Christians are to pray for their enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:44\">MAT 5:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:28\">LUK 6:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:60\">ACT 7:60</a></p>\n<h3>Christians are to pray for one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18\">EPH 6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:25\">1TH 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:22\">PHM 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:18-Heb13:19\">HEB 13:18–13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14-Jas5:16\">JAS 5:14–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16\">1JN 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Christians are to prayer for rulers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:1–2:2</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of pleas made to Jesus Christ on behalf of others</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:5-Matt8:13\">MAT 8:5–8:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:1-Luke7:10\">LUK 7:1–7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:21-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:21–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:24-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:24–7:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:14-Matt17:20\">MAT 17:14–17:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:14-Mark9:29\">MRK 9:14–9:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:37-Luke9:42\">LUK 9:37–9:42</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of notable prayers of intercession</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:14-2Kgs19:19\">2KI 19:14–19:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:14-Isa37:20\">ISA 37:14–37:20</a> <em>Hezekiah for deliverance</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:21-Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:21–8:23</a> <em>Ezra for a safe journey</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:1-Dan9:19\">DAN 9:1–9:19</a> <em>Daniel for Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:6-John17:26\">JHN 17:6–17:26</a> <em>Jesus Christ for his disciples</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:15-Eph1:21\">EPH 1:15–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14-Eph3:21\">EPH 3:14–3:21</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:9-Col1:13\">COL 1:9–1:13</a> <em>Paul for the believers in Colosse</em></p>",
